Joseph Olaoluwa An Executive Director of the United Bank for Africa Plc, Abdoul Dia, has resigned from the lender’s board. According to a notice filed by the bank to the Nigerian Stock Exchange, Dia’s resignation is effective May 6, 2020. The Board of UBA expressed its appreciation to Dia for his contributions to the UBA Group. Copyright PUNCH.
